    "recap_headline": "Princeton University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "PRINCETON, N.J. -\nThe Tigers start 2-1 in Ivy League play, as they fall short 6-3 in the final game of the series against Cornell.\nWill Robbins\nopened up the scoring for the Tigers in the first with a two run double, taking a 2-1 lead after Cornell opened up scoring at the top of the inning.\nCornell tied things up in the third making it a 2-2 score.\nPrinceton answered back in the fourth inning, taking a 3-2 lead after\nJake Kernodle\nhit a home run, his second of the season.\nCornell took a late 6-3 lead and ultimately a win after putting up four runs between the eighth and ninth innings.\nWith\nLiam Kinneen\nworking the mound for six innings, followed by\nRyan Penney\nand\nCharlie Wolf\nto close, the pitching trio combined for nine strikeouts in the loss.\nThe Tigers will take on Seton Hall on Wednesday with first pitch scheduled for 4 PM.",
